exif:ImageDescription: "I remember when I first came out here, I wanted to take a woman friend of mine out dancing one night. I asked a pal where to go and he bang naming a lot of little hideaways. I told him that I had heard about the wild life in Southern California and was fairly champing at the bit to get at it. Gravely he shook his head. ...You...ve got a lot to learn, my boy. If you go out to one of the big spots you...ll get your name linked with hers and well, don...t you see?... I didn...t. I still don...t. As near as I can get it, everything is all right in Hollywood provided no gossip columnist sees you. ... The cardinal sin of Hollywood is to be caught" - Errol Flynn
